2- Why don't you have any attempt to call 911 during the night?

What would be the worst moment for two girls from an urban environment, lost in the middle of a tropical jungle?
Do you agree with me that this worst moment would be to spend the night in the forest?! Exhausted, cold, with animals moving on the ground, animal movement in the dark forest, a plague of insects, rain spray, hunger, thirst and darkness everywhere. This would undoubtedly be the time when they would most try to connect to an emergency number, but they didn't.

Lisanne and Kris decided on their own, to continue the trail past the viewpoint, when they realized they couldn't make it back before nightfall, or because they really got lost and disoriented, they decided to make the first two calls in the late afternoon of April 1st. . comments.text: No one did this to them. These 2 girls caused their own deaths. They did a jungle trek spontaneously without a plan, did not wear appropriate clothing, did not bring enough water and food. Made a fatal decision to continue hiking past the summit. Called for help when they got caught in the jungle at dusk and had to stay there overnight but made a fatal decision to continue walking the next morning when fog hit and walked further and further away. One of them got injured, Kris broke her pelvis fell into a ravine and her best friend went after her but injured her foot on the way down. They couldn't escape and died of hunger, hypothermia, shock. if they had just stayed at the spot of their first call for help they would have been found the next day or 2 days later. Don't blame this on any cartel or indigenous people. Their multiple poor decision making proved fatal. They didn't respect the jungle and it's dangers.
